<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="124" type="description">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1146,2072]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[136,274,1146,1172]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Description</emphasis>
:—Perennial herbs. Roots succulent, tuberose. Stem to 
<quantity box="[875,942,1146,1173]" metricMagnitude="-1" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="20.0">20 cm</quantity>
tall, branched, proximally sparsely pubescent, distally glabrous. Leaves 2‒3-ternate; blade triangular, 
<quantity box="[750,832,1182,1209]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.5" metricValueMax="8.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="5.5" valueMax="8.0" valueMin="3.0">3‒8 cm</quantity>
long and broad; leaflets orbicular or broadly ovate, 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1‒2 cm</quantity>
long and broad, herbaceous, glabrous on both surfaces, green on adaxial surface, pale green on abaxial surface, base rounded or subcordate, apex obtuse, 3-lobate; lobes entire or inconspicuously 1‒3-crenate; veins flat adaxially, raised abaxially; petiole slender, 
<quantity box="[438,524,1290,1317]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="5.0" metricValueMax="7.0" metricValueMin="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="5.0" valueMax="7.0" valueMin="3.0">3‒7 cm</quantity>
long; stipule membranous, inconspicuous. Inflorescence compound monochasia, corymbiform. Pedicel slender, 
<quantity box="[487,572,1326,1353]" metricMagnitude="-2" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" metricValueMax="2.0" metricValueMin="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="cm" value="1.5" valueMax="2.0" valueMin="1.0">1‒2 cm</quantity>
long. Flowers bisexual, erect. Sepals 4‒6, elliptic, ca. 
<quantity box="[1202,1269,1326,1353]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
long, ca. 
<quantity box="[1385,1452,1326,1353]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
broad, white. Stamens 11‒15, ca. 
<quantity box="[513,578,1362,1389]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long; filaments filiform, ca. 
<quantity box="[900,964,1362,1389]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, white; anthers narrowly oblong, ca. 
<quantity metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="1.0">1 mm</quantity>
long, apex obtuse, pale yellow. Carpels 11‒18, sessile, ca. 
<quantity box="[844,909,1398,1425]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="2.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="2.0">2 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous; ovary narrowly fusiform, nearly smooth, ca. 
<quantity box="[271,357,1434,1461]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.5" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="1.5">1.5 mm</quantity>
long; style straight, ca. 
<quantity box="[624,710,1434,1461]" metricMagnitude="-4" metricUnit="m" metricValue="6.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="0.6">0.6 mm</quantity>
long; stigma inconspicuous, point-like. Achenes sessile, ca. 
<quantity box="[1387,1452,1434,1461]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="3.0" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="mm" value="3.0">3 mm</quantity>
long, glabrous; body subulate-terete, inconspicuously ribbed; style persistent.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
<subSubSection pageId="3" pageNumber="124" type="distribution">
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1146,2072]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,486,1506,1532]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Distribution and habitat</emphasis>
: 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Zeng, Q. Yuan &amp; Q. E. Yang" authorityYear="2021" box="[503,771,1506,1532]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanhuaense">
<emphasis box="[503,771,1506,1532]" italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Thalictrum nanhuaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is currently known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[1164,1212,1507,1533]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">type</typeStatus>
locality, i.e. Nanhua county in central 
<collectingRegion box="[333,527,1542,1569]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[539,606,1542,1568]" name="China" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[622,692,1542,1568]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,214,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[170,1417,190,1053]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution of Thalictrum fargesii (▲) and T. nanhuaense (■)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413305/files/figure.png" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). It grows in northern subtropical thickets dominated by 
<taxonomicName authority="Franchet (1890: 187)" authorityName="Franchet" authorityPageNumber="187" authorityYear="1890" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Fabaceae" genus="Dalbergia" kingdom="Plantae" order="Fabales" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="yunnanensis">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Dalbergia yunnanensis</emphasis>
Franchet (1890: 187)
</taxonomicName>
on slopes at an altitude of 
<quantity box="[819,904,1578,1605]" metricMagnitude="3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="1.6" pageId="3" pageNumber="124" unit="m" value="1600.0">1600 m</quantity>
above sea level.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="3.[136,1452,1146,2072]" box="[189,1103,1614,1641]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,313,1614,1640]" pageId="3" pageNumber="124">Phenology</emphasis>
:—Flowering from July to August; fruiting from August to September.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
