<paragraph blockId="6.[136,1452,158,436]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[189,256,158,184]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Notes</emphasis>
:—From a morphological perspective, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Y. P. Zeng, Q. Yuan &amp; Q. E. Yang" authorityYear="2021" box="[695,961,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="nanhuaense">
<emphasis box="[695,961,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Thalictrum nanhuaense</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is similar to 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Franchet ex Finet &amp; Gagnepain" authorityYear="1903" box="[1112,1225,158,184]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fargesii">
<emphasis box="[1112,1225,158,184]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">T. fargesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
(
<figureCitation box="[1241,1321,158,184]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="4.[136,229,1953,1975]" captionTargetBox="[212,1375,190,1929]" captionTargetId="figure-19@4.[212,1375,190,1929]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 4. Syntype sheets (A‒D) of Thalictrum fargesii." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413309" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413309/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Figs. 4</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation box="[1334,1348,158,185]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="5.[136,229,1928,1950]" captionTargetBox="[170,1417,190,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-18@5.[170,1417,190,1903]" captionTargetPageId="5" captionText="FIGURE 5. Thalictrum fargesii in the wild (Pingwu county in northern Sichuan province, China). A. Habitat. B. Habit. C. Roots. D. Portion of stem. E. Leaf (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). F. Leaflet (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). G. Flower. H. Sepal (left: adaxial side; right: abaxial side). I. Stamens. J. Carpels. K. Aggregate fruit. L. Achenes (immature). Photographed by Y.P. Zeng." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413317" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413317/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">5</figureCitation>
) in habit and having larger sepals up to 
<quantity box="[477,542,194,221]" metricMagnitude="-3" metricUnit="m" metricValue="4.0" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" unit="mm" value="4.0">4 mm</quantity>
long and persistent at anthesis and straight styles, but differs by its succulent and tuberose (vs. fibrous and slender) roots, filiform (vs. clavate) filaments, point-like (vs. oblong and narrowly winged) stigmas, and subulate-terete (vs. lunate-fusiform) achenes. Geographically, 
<taxonomicName authorityName="Franchet ex Finet &amp; Gagnepain" authorityYear="1903" box="[987,1101,266,292]" class="Magnoliopsida" family="Ranunculaceae" genus="Thalictrum" kingdom="Plantae" order="Ranunculales" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" phylum="Tracheophyta" rank="species" species="fargesii">
<emphasis box="[987,1101,266,292]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">T. fargesii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is widely distributed in 
<collectingRegion box="[1374,1447,266,292]" country="China" name="Anhui" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Anhui</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[136,263,302,328]" country="China" name="Chongqing" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Chongqing</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[274,349,302,328]" country="China" name="Fujian" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Fujian</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[359,433,302,328]" country="China" name="Gansu" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Gansu</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[443,542,302,328]" country="China" name="Guizhou" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Guizhou</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[553,629,303,329]" country="China" name="Henan" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Henan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[639,710,302,328]" country="China" name="Hubei" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Hubei</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[721,798,303,329]" country="China" name="Hunan" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Hunan</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[809,893,302,328]" country="China" name="Jiangxi" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Jiangxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[903,996,302,328]" country="China" name="Shaanxi" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Shaanxi</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingRegion box="[1006,1099,302,328]" country="China" name="Sichuan" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Sichuan</collectingRegion>
, and 
<collectingRegion box="[1157,1257,302,328]" country="China" name="Zhejiang" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Zhejiang</collectingRegion>
provinces, 
<collectingCountry box="[1384,1451,302,328]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">China</collectingCountry>
(
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, W. T. &amp; Wang, S. H." box="[143,375,338,365]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" pagination="502 - 592" refId="ref2597" refString="Wang, W. T. &amp; Wang, S. H. (1979) Thalictrum L. In: Anonymous (Ed.) Flora Reipublicae Popularis Sinicae, vol. 27. Science Press, Beijing, pp. 502 - 592." type="book chapter" year="1979">Wang &amp; Wang 1979</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Fu, D. Z. &amp; Zhu, G. H." box="[386,562,338,365]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" pagination="282 - 302" refId="ref2258" refString="Fu, D. Z. &amp; Zhu, G. H. (2001) Thalictrum Linnaeus. In: Wu, Z. Y., Raven, P. H. &amp; Hong, D. Y. (Eds.) Flora of China, vol. 6. Science Press, Beijing &amp; Missouri Botanical Garden Press, St. Louis, pp. 282 - 302." type="book chapter" year="2001">Fu &amp; Zhu 2001</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Li, J. Y. &amp; Liu, H. J. &amp; Wang, Y. Z. &amp; Xie, L." box="[573,726,338,364]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" pagination="57 - 58" refId="ref2388" refString="Li, J. Y., Liu, H. J., Wang, Y. Z. &amp; Xie, L. (2016) A new synonymy in Thalictrum (Ranunculaceae). Phytotaxa 286: 57 - 58. https: // doi. org / 10.11646 / phytotaxa. 286.1.8" type="journal article" year="2016">
Li 
<emphasis box="[604,661,338,364]" italics="true" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">et al.</emphasis>
2016
</bibRefCitation>
, 
<bibRefCitation author="Wang, W. T." box="[736,881,338,365]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127" refId="ref2503" refString="Wang, W. T. (2018 a) Thalictrum (Ranunculaceae) in China. Peking University Press, Beijing, 376 pp." type="book" year="2018">Wang 2018a</bibRefCitation>
). Our new species is currently known only from its 
<typeStatus box="[136,184,375,401]" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">type</typeStatus>
locality, i.e. Nanhua county in central 
<collectingRegion box="[624,818,374,401]" country="China" name="Yunnan" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Yunnan province</collectingRegion>
, 
<collectingCountry box="[830,897,374,400]" name="China" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">China</collectingCountry>
(
<figureCitation box="[914,983,374,400]" captionStart="FIGURE 3" captionStartId="3.[136,229,1078,1100]" captionTargetBox="[194,1393,214,1029]" captionTargetId="figure-18@3.[170,1417,190,1053]" captionTargetPageId="3" captionText="FIGURE 3. Distribution of Thalictrum fargesii (▲) and T. nanhuaense (■)." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.5413305" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/5413305/files/figure.png" pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Fig. 3</figureCitation>
). A detailed comparison between the two species is given in 
<tableCitation box="[347,431,410,436]" captionStart="TABLE 1" captionStartId="6.[136,224,484,508]" captionText="TABLE 1. Comparison between Thalictrum fargesii and T. nanhuaense." pageId="6" pageNumber="127">Table 1</tableCitation>
.
